events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero had 20 points, 10 rebounds and 11 assists for his second career triple-double, overcoming early shooting woes to help the Orlando Magic beat the New Orleans Pelicans 121-106 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero has 2nd career triple-double, Magic beat Pelicans 121-106

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 31 points and the Washington Wizards snapped a five-game losing streak with a 109-102 win over the Sacramento Kings on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma scores 31, Wizards snap 5-game skid with 109-102 win over Kings

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 26 points, Dillon Brooks had 23 before he was ejected from the game and the Rockets won their seventh straight, 127-117 over the Chicago Bulls on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green scores 26 points as Rockets win 7th straight, beat Bulls 127-117

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had his third straight game with at least 30 points. He made his two biggest plays on the other end of the floor.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard sparkles, Antetokounmpo returns to help Bucks hold off Nets, 115-108

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 34 points, nine rebounds and eight assists and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Utah Jazz 113-97 on Thursday night to move into the sixth and final guaranteed playoff position in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic leads Mavericks past Jazz, 113-97, into 6th place in West

events.name: New York Knicks at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Michael Porter Jr. has the green light to not only shoot but visit Cabo San Lucas, Mexico, whenever he wants. His coach will even pick up the tab.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porter and Jokic turn in big nights, lead Nuggets to 113-100 win over Knicks

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 30 points, Eric Gordon added 21 off the bench and the Phoenix Suns beat the Atlanta Hawks 128-115 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker scores 30 points, Suns get hot from 3-point range to beat Hawks 128-115
